html
  head
    title Forms Demo

    include header

  body

    include _nav

    mixin select(lclass)
      div(class=" select-style #{lclass}")
          select
            option( value="volvo") VolvO
            option( value="saab") Saab
            option( value="mercedes") Mercedes
            option( value="audi") Audi



    .row
      .col-12

        h2.divide-section Forms
        p
          |Almost no extra work for forms. Grid can be applied to form elements.
          |Make form creation super easy and customizable

        h3 Basic Input Element
        p
          | All input elements have to be wrapped in some element (div, li, p, etc.) with
          | the class
          code field
          | . The
          code= "<input>"
          | tag itself needs to have the class
          code input
          | . That's all you need!


        .preview-box
          form.row

            input(class="input col-12" type="text" placeholder="Text input")

            input( class="input col-12" type="email" placeholder="Email input")

            input( class="input col-12" type="password" placeholder="Password input")

            textarea( class="textarea col-12" placeholder="Textarea").preview-box

        h3 Collapse horizontal space
        p Add <code>.collapse</code> to form

        .preview-box
           form.row.collapse

            input(class="input col-12" type="text" placeholder="Text input")

            input( class="input col-12" type="email" placeholder="Email input")

            input( class="input col-12" type="password" placeholder="Password input")

            textarea( class="textarea col-12" placeholder="Textarea")

        
        h3 Control input size
        p Use grid system to control width. Also you can use  <code>.width-per-{precentage-value}</code>.

